Did you miss me? I missed you.

I’ve been working up a storm for you guys while raising my newborn :) 

I’m super excited to share all the new things coming, but if you want to be the FIRST to know then you MUST subscribe to my newsletter. Head over to my site inspiredfoody.com to add your email in the pop up, in the about page, or send me a message!

ALEXA tell everyone “Inspired Foody is back AND better than ever”! 

More recipe videos. Baby content. Cooking Classes. Online Courses. AND MORE! Stay tuned.

Looking back at the last year or two and thinking woah… 

It’s been a long road of crazy surprises, hurdles, and pivots but I wouldn’t change it for the world. 

& I know I keep disappearing on this platform, but I’m making a promise to you that this time… it’s different.

I’ve been working so hard on what I’m about to launch. And I’m even more excited to share it all with you. 

To start off, though, I’m officially inviting you all to TWO FREE zoom classes this week. 

1. THURSDAY 5/4 is a free class on how to make top-down recipe videos 
2. FRIDAY 5/5 is a free cooking class on how to make challah! 

I’ll be dishing out all my secrets and tricks. You don’t want to miss it. 

Subscribe to my newsletter on my site for my info!! 

Can’t wait to see you there ❤️☀️

6. That’s how many years I’ve been working in the food industry. And by food industry, I mean running my own company from the ground up. 

I’ve definitely hit some roadblocks, challenges, milestones, and achievements. I wouldn’t trade it all for the world. 

I want to use my knowledge and spread it to all of you. Whether it be how to get started in your kitchen for the first time or how to create top-down recipe videos… I want to teach you. 

Comment your email or message me below if you’re interested! 

I’ll be teaching a FREE zoom class on how to create recipe videos tomorrow at 12:15pm and another FREE zoom class on how to make challah this Friday at 12:15pm ❤️ 

Hope to see you there!

YOU’RE IN LUCK! 

I’m hosting a 1 hour FREE zoom session today at 12:15 pm PST to dish out some of my tips and tricks to teach YOU how to do it. FOR THOSE OF YOU WHO JOIN, will also get a FREE downloadable guide with EXTRA info! 

You don’t wanna miss it! 

Will be posting the link in my stories :)
Want to gain your kitchen confidence? Start by joining my 12pm PST FREE cooking class today! Link in stories ☀️

Consider this your OFFICIAL invite to my Kitchen Basics course!! 

Whether you’re afraid of picking up a kitchen tool or in the kitchen often… this course is for YOU! I find that many people are afraid to be in their kitchens, try new tools and ingredients, so I made a course to get you started. Moving out for the first time? Freshman in college? Trying to learn how to cook? This course is for YOU!! I’m here to teach you what tools and ingredients you need to build your kitchen and the basic recipes you should know aka rice, pasta, chicken, etc!!

Food videos are all about having an appetite. So, if you love food and love seeing it transform from something simple to something beautiful and delicious, then that’s all that matters. 

This is an ENTRY level course for those of you who have professional cameras OR cellphones but are new to shooting video. 

You’ll have lifetime access to all course materials, videos and the online community. 

This course was designed 100% with you in mind. 

Catch 15% off THIS WEEK ONLY for $422!!

Delicious Gluten-Free Lemon Blueberry Cake! 🍋💙✨

🌟 Made with love and top-quality ingredients, including butter, brown sugar, lemon zest, lemon juice, vanilla extract, eggs, gluten-free flour, salt, almond meal, and plump blueberries.

✨ Prepare to be amazed as these flavors dance in your mouth. This cake is both gluten-free and full of delightful texture. 🌾🍽️

🎂💖 This gluten-free lemon blueberry cake is a true crowd-pleaser! Perfect for any occasion, it’s sure to impress both gluten-free and non-gluten-free guests alike. Share the love and the joy of this delectable treat with your loved ones. 🥰🎉

Introducing Baby's First Meal: Nutritious Oatmeal Delight! 🍼🥣✨

Exciting news, mommies and daddies! Get ready for a journey of delicious and nutritious baby food recipes. 🍽️💕 Starting with a milestone moment, we're thrilled to share the recipe for baby oatmeal - a perfect first food for your little bundle of joy. 🌾👶

🌟 Here's what makes this baby oatmeal recipe special:

🥣 Simple and gentle: With just two ingredients - oats and water (or breast milk/formula) - I’m keeping it pure and natural. No unnecessary additives or fillers, ensuring a gentle introduction to solid foods for your little one.

🍼 Customizable and controlled: We'll begin with a maximum of 1 tablespoon a day, allowing your baby's delicate tummy to adjust and appreciate this new culinary experience. Remember, every baby is different, so it's crucial to consult with your pediatrician and consider factors like weight and interest before starting solids.

📚 Find the detailed recipe on the blog, where I’ll  be sharing more baby food recipes every Monday. From purees to finger foods, I’ve got you covered as we embark on this exciting feeding journey together. 🍓🥕🥦

📹 Stay tuned for the video demonstration, which will be posted tomorrow. Watch as I guide you through each step, ensuring a seamless and enjoyable cooking experience. Let's get inspired and empower each other on this beautiful parenting adventure! 🌟👩‍👧

👉 Share your thoughts, ask questions, and leave reviews on the website. I’m here to support you every step of the way, creating nourishing meals for your precious little ones. Together, let's embrace this new chapter of parenthood with joy and excitement! 🌈👶💖

#BabysFirstMeal #NutritiousOatmeal #StartingSolids #PureAndNatural #BabyFoodRecipes #InspiredParenting #MommyBlogger #FeedingJourney #ParentingAdventure #StayTuned

👉 Watch the recipe video now for BABY OATMEAL and witness the joy of introducing your baby to the wonders of food. I hope this recipe inspires you to create lovingly prepared meals for your little bundle of joy. Let’s embrace parenthood with love and deliciousness! 🌟👩‍👧

Indulge in Decadence: Heavenly Three-Layer Cake! 🍰✨

Get ready to experience pure bliss with my all-time favorite recipe, the irresistible three-layer cake! 🎂✨ Each layer offers a symphony of flavors and textures, creating a dessert that's sure to impress. Prepare to be swept away on a journey of decadence and delight. 🌟😍

✨ Let's dive into the layers of this creation:

Bottom Layer:

Sink your fork into a moist and rich chocolate heaven. The combination of separated eggs, sugar, cocoa powder, water, and self-rising flour creates a fudgy delight that will have you coming back for more. 🍫🍮

Middle Layer:

Elevate the indulgence with a creamy dreamland. Whipped heavy whipping cream, a small box of vanilla instant pudding, and milk come together to create a luscious filling that adds a touch of sweetness and velvety smoothness. 🥛💫

Top Layer:

Experience the ultimate chocolate pleasure. Melted bittersweet chocolate combined with milk or heavy whipping cream and butter create a glossy and rich ganache that beautifully coats the top layer, adding a luxurious finishing touch. 🍫🍨

📚 Find the complete recipe for this divine three-layer cake on my blog: inspiredfoody.com. Delve into a world of baking wonders and discover more tantalizing recipes to satisfy your sweet tooth. 🍰💕

✨ Celebrate life's special moments or simply treat yourself to an unforgettable dessert experience. With each forkful, let this cake transport you to a realm of pure joy and indulgence. Share the love and savor every bite! 😋💖

The world of baby food aka introduction to rice cereal. 🌾👶 Specially crafted with love, this recipe is designed to introduce your little one to new flavors and textures. Get ready for an adventure in taste! 🌟💕

✨ Here's what makes this baby rice cereal recipe special:

🍚 Nutrient-packed grains: I opt for short-grain rice, specifically Lundberg brand, to ensure lower levels of arsenic. Your baby's health and well-being are top priority.

🍼 Customizable liquid: Choose from breast milk, formula, water, or unsweetened plain non-dairy milk as the liquid base for the cereal. This allows you to cater to your baby's individual needs and preferences.

🍲 Cooking and blending: With just the right amount of water for cooking the rice and additional liquid for blending, we create a smooth and creamy consistency that's easy for your baby to enjoy.

🌈 Optional flavors: Expand your baby's palate with a range of delicious puree options, including apple, banana, peanut butter, pear, plain whole milk yogurt, spinach, and sweet potato. Each adds a delightful twist to the cereal, making mealtime a playful and enjoyable experience.

📚 Find the complete recipe on the blog, inspiredfoody.com, where I’m dedicated to sharing more wholesome and nutritious baby food recipes. Empower yourself with the knowledge and creativity to nourish your little one with love. 🍓🥕🥦

👉 Experiment with different flavors and combinations, tailoring the cereal to your baby's developing taste buds. Watch their excitement grow as they explore new flavors with each spoonful. Let's make mealtime a moment of joy and discovery! 😋👶💖

#BabysFirstCereal #WholesomeDelights #NourishingBabyFood #IntroducingFlavors #InspiredParenting #MealtimeAdventures #HomemadeBabyFood #BabyFoodRecipes #NutritionForLittleOnes #LoveInEverySpoon

Baby Rice Cereal ✨ the perfect way to lean your baby onto solids. Take this easy foundation and mix it with your favorite purée or just add cinnamon! Your baby will love it.

🍽️ A crowd-pleaser: Whether you're hosting a backyard gathering or enjoying a cozy meal with loved ones, this asparagus lasagne is sure to impress. Its unique flavors and lightness make it an irresistible choice for summer dining.

📚 Find the complete recipe for this mouthwatering dish on my blog, inspiredfoody.com. Explore my collection of recipes that celebrate the joy of seasonal cooking. 🍅🌽🥕

Baby Quinoa 🤩 another great foundation to start your little one on. It’s best to start your baby on the easy cereal ranging from rice, oats, and quinoa and see which your baby likes most. From there, you take it a step up by adding purées to enhance the flavors and help introduce sweet/savory/in between notes. Recipes on the blog!
BABY QUINOA! Easy to make and easy to feed. Introduce solids to your baby with a simple recipe like this. More on the blog!

Get ready to tantalize your taste buds with our sensational herb jam salmon. 🍃🍓🌶️ As seen on KTLA, this dish stole the show and now it's ready to become a star in your kitchen. Indulge in the perfect balance of sweetness and tanginess, enhanced by a medley of aromatic herbs. It's a true crowd-pleaser! 🌟😋

✨ Here's why this herb jam salmon deserves a spot on your menu:

🌿 Sweet and tangy glaze: The combination of flavorful jam, a hint of spiciness from sriracha, and a touch of sweetness creates a glaze that elevates the natural richness of the salmon. Each bite is an explosion of delightful flavors that will keep you craving more.

🌱 Versatile herb toppings: my favorite herb topping mixture of parsley, dill, and mint adds a refreshing and vibrant touch. However, feel free to use whatever herbs you have on hand to personalize this dish. Get creative and let your taste buds guide you!

🔥 Oven or grill: Whether you're hosting a backyard BBQ or prefer the convenience of your oven, this salmon recipe is super versatile. It can be perfectly cooked to perfection in either, allowing you to enjoy it in any setting.

🍽️ Recipe on the blog: Discover the secrets to making this mouthwatering herb jam salmon on my blog, inspiredfoody.com. Unleash your inner chef and explore a world of delightful recipes that will inspire your culinary adventures. 🌍🍴

✨ Prepare to impress your guests or simply indulge in a restaurant-quality dish at home. Let the sweet and tangy glaze, infused with a symphony of herbs, transport your taste buds to a realm of pure satisfaction. Get ready for a culinary experience you won't soon forget! 😍🔥🌿

Inspired Foody here! Hiya :) 

I’m Emma. I’m a new mama, entrepreneur, and food blogger in LA. I enjoy every aspect of food — cooking, baking, photographing, filming, styling, sharing, and eating. I am self-taught and always hungry. I specialize in food photography, top-down recipe videos, and culinary direction. My goal is to inspire others to get in their kitchen… whether it be to eat or to cook. My passion lays in food. 

I'm selectively seeking a few exclusive partners for the year. Work with me and you’ll get monthly content, cross-promotion, and a guaranteed trusted spokesperson. 

Want to work together or know someone who’d be interested? Comment below or send a message! ❤️ 

📸: @shotbymarom
